HEADWORD: Horologiography
<hw>Hor`o*lo`gi*og"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
horologe + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An account of
instruments that show the hour.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of constructing clocks or dials;
